  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then-- I also-- you know, I-- last year, I was appointed ambassador to the Tel Aviv foundation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they are totally familiar with my media activities in that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And also there is a monument-- a-- a monument in-- in the Spiegel Park near the Tel Aviv Hilton where I am-- where my bronze figure there is cast for life, I hope.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And by the way, you are or may not be aware, I am one of the founders of the Holocaust Museum in Washington-- one of the original founders.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, that's right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I'm also-- what's called--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the-- and-- and to verify also that, which has been documented, and-- and the most important thing that to-- to-- will be testimony to the various war crimes trials where I was witness in a variety of cities, including Chicago, Dusseldorf, in Vienna, in Stuttgart, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] plus others where I wasn't witness, but I had to give testimony in writing.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And most important--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Here-- there is here in LA at the Holocaust Monument, you will see inscribed [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the-- The Fred Kort Family Foundation as sponsors and founder on one of the pillars, which is dedicated to the fallen brethren from Treblinka.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then we have a wall, which is dedicated to my family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't think they blew it up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I revisited first Treblinka about four weeks after I-- after I was finally liberated when I got away, out from the forest and so on.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And what I saw then was just the slabs of the many barracks that were there, which would indicate to me they didn't do away with it.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think they only set matches to the barracks, because the foundations are all there.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
